<br>
Her place in the Amazons speaks of her way of living. She is loyal and alert toward those she respects and owes her personal well being to. Unfortunately, some friendships have come before the Amazons in Sartha's mind in the past. She travels often, and for long spaces of time. Yet she always returns to her Athelfi, showing just how much she truly depends on them to be her family. They are precious to her as many things never could be. Sartha can be very unfeeling and indifferent, but it is clear just how much the Amazons mean to her. <br>
<br>
She has had two daughters in her lifetime- Sarin and Brin. Sarin was the result of a dead lover, a treasured child that was the only thing remaining to Sar at that time. Before Sartha came to Themiscrya, she lost Sarin in a war between another tribe and a tribe of men. It was after Sarin's death that Sartha came to meet Hippolyte and become an Amazon of Themiscrya. Brin was the daughter she had with her first and only husband- Wolfen. Wolfen left Sartha soon after the birth of Brin, and the child grew quickly due to the basis of Sartha's origin. But Brin grew to hate her mother, and later ran off. Sartha has never seen her since, but believes that her daughter will be fine, as she always was. <br>
<br>
Sartha has lived a long, harsh life of much death and lonliness. Much of her time was and is spent alone, even in Themiscrya and the other tribes. No doubt, she will remain alone. <br>
